
CLone allows you to clone a repository. That may be a local repository, networked or on git hub.

What git clone is actually doing is pulling a remote repository into your desired location. Git clone is ashortcut command for adding a remote repo and pulling it. Git clone can do the set up and pull with one command.

When developers work on projects typically they will clone repositories locally while they work on the code.

Git provides sereval tools for ensuring your cloned repository is up to date with the master repository and ways for you to push your changes to the orgin.
